FG-502 — Limited Lift with Undertakings (Security ≠ Cash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Propose non-cash undertakings to justify a partial lift of a stay.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Pair each risk with an undertaking (escrow item; weekly reporting; hold-harmless; compliance declaration). Keep the lift narrow (one ¶/claim) and time-boxed.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 4-row Risk → Undertaking table and a two-line ask.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Lift stay as to ¶2 only; weekly vendor reports + officer declaration; sunset 21 days; status day 14.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Security shows seriousness without cash barriers.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A locked pad with a small window opened over “¶2 only.”

⸻

FG-503 — Clarify Stay Scope (Who • What • When)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Write one scope sentence: who is bound, what text, and for how long.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote the exact paragraph/line stayed; limit to parties only; add sunset and status; carve out non-party vendors.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a one-sentence scope paragraph for your live stay.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Scope: stay ¶3 as to parties only; vendors carved out; sunset in 21 days; status at day 14.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Precision beats overbreadth on review.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A bracket around a single paragraph with a small clock tab.

⸻

FG-504 — After-Opinion Admin Stay (Orderly Transition)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Post-opinion, ask for a 7–14 day admin stay to avoid disruption—no merits change.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Identify the operational choke point (printing, payroll, system cutover); tie to one paragraph; propose status + short sunset; attach tick-box order.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line admin-stay application with two operational pins.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Relief: 10-day admin stay of ¶3 to avoid reprint (Vendor PO Ex A); status at day 5; sunset 09/30.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Short pauses prevent big messes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A printer icon paused with a 10-day ribbon.

⸻

FG-505 — Stay-to-Report Conversion (Weekly Status + Auto-Lift)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Trade a broad stay for weekly reporting + automatic lift on date.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Propose reports at day 7/14; sunset fixed; scope one ¶; include a “no third-party obligations” line.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft the conversion paragraph and a 4-item reporting checklist.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Convert stay to weekly reports and auto-lift 09/30; scope ¶3; no obligations on non-party vendors; status template attached.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Visibility substitutes for freeze.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A calendar card marked Day 7/14 and a green “AUTO-LIFT” tag.
